channel.title: Trouble With CMD
channel.description:
Hi, before reading this you need to know that I wasn't sure where to post this, and not to ask me for teamviewer info, because I am not going to let you see my ip address.
With that said I will get on with it.
Ok so I need to change my ip address and I want to see my ipconfig info so I went to run and typed ipconfig, the little box came up but went away almost directly after. I also tried to go to CMD and tried to type ipconfig but it said something like "ipconfig is not recognized as an internal or external command" I also tried ipconfig/all but that didn't work. Someone's help would be greatly appreciated.
P.S: if anyone knows how to change my ip address I need to know that too but I still need this problem fixed. Oh and it's a Windows XP computer of that helps.

item.title: Trouble With CMD
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

[quote=“Native^, post:16, topic:432926”][quote author=TiVo link=topic=535636.msg3925359#msg3925359 date=1330162198]
Only noobs are too afraid to go on TeamViewer because their afraid someone will “hack” them with their IP.
[/quote]

  1. Moparscape is not a spoonfeeding community.
  2. If you actually want to program a server, learn it. Don’t let someone do it for you.
  3. Teamviewer is gay.[/quote]

I can agree with the first two, but your third one is completely unjustified. If you ever find yourself working with a 3D modeler and are trying to understand a design, goodluck achieving that without something as convenient as teamviewer.

item.dc:creator: @Xevi Xevi
item.description:
@Xevi wrote:

[quote=“zyle1992, post:11, topic:432926”]fe80::72f1:a1ff:feb7:2a8d/64

That’s my IPv6 Address. Doesn’t matter much, because people can easily use proxys, and spoof their mac address.

As for OP, edit your PATH variable to include your system32 folder.(Usually C:\Program Files\Windows\System32), but it can change for your system.[/quote]Wow… It Works!, Thanks A Ton Man I Would Rep You If I Could, But I Cant ;(]. Anyways I Have 2 More Questions.

  1. Was I Right To Put It In The Path For “User Variables For…”, Or Should I Switch It To The Path In “System Variables”.

  2. How Do I Change My IP Address, On A Server I Have 2 Accounts, So I Would Like To Know How To Do That So I Can Vote On Each. Thanks Guys For All The Help! And If You Do In fact Fix My Problems, I Will Rep You If Possible.
